An open letter to a guy whom I know I don't deserve.  Hi,  I hope this letter finds you.  
 First of all, thank you for making me feel loved,  cared for, and happy for a span of what three weeks HAHAHAHAH.  You are the most consistent, brilliant,  caring guy I have talked to. You learned some words in my dialect,  you watched Zoey's extraordinary playlist that I recommended, you never skipped a day reminding me to take my medicine, we talked about our traumas, and you understood me.  We had a lot in common: the love for Taylor Swift,  the love for Hamilton, and our traumas. HAHAHHAHA. I will never forget you and how I woke up with my alarm clock helpless and then heard you singing, satisfied- that will be one of my top 5 most amazing things that happened to me. I was enchanted to meet you, but please be in love with someone who will love you the way I could never.  Be in love with someone who will give you assurance and will risk for you because, trust me, you are worth the risk,  but I am not courageous enough. I'm sorry for being scared; I'm sorry for giving up too quickly, and I'm sorry for hurting you.  I hope that you will believe in love because you deserve the love the world has to offer. I hope we can meet again,  and if we ever meet again, I hope you reach your dream of being a doctor.  PADAYON FUTURE DOCTOR! I will always be here cheering for you!

We both felt it, but kept silent about it. 

I remember back in 2010, when I was still in HS. Nagkagusto din ako sa isang guy. I considered him as my first ever love. Deep inside, I felt that he liked me too. Lagi ko siyang nahuhuling nakatingin sa'kin. Buong HS, hindi ko ipinakita sa kanya na gusto ko siya (not in front of him). If he was (near) around at tinutukso ako, I always say "Hindi ah. Bakit sana (gusto ko siya)". But the whole class knew na super crush ko siya. Even his bff who's fortunately my great dear friend too. I made sure to always attend to his basketball match, cheering for him from afar. Back in 2012 (my birthday), kinukulit nila siya at tinatanong kung sino yung may birthday sa araw na yun. He spelled every letter of my name out loud, "Si I - S - L  - E". Then our classmates teased and laughed at us.
